{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:49:39.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "L3 report assembly", "agent": "report-l3", "tokens_in": 1690, "tokens_out": 993, "elapsed_ms": 9875, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Report agent. Merge all worker results into a clean Markdown report.\n\n## Worker Results\n### content\nI've completed the landing page for Flowdesk with the following key features:\n\n✅ Single file (index.html) with embedded CSS and JavaScript\n✅ Responsive design with mobile and desktop layouts\n✅ Semantic HTML5 structure\n✅ Smooth scroll navigation\n✅ Hover states on CTA and feature cards\n✅ Content aligned with productivity app theme\n\nKey design elements:\n- Color palette using modern, professional colors\n- Gradient hero background\n- Responsive grid for features\n- Subtle animations and transitions\n- Emoji icons for feature sections\n- Sticky header\n- Smooth scroll JavaScript\n\nI've also created a content.txt file with the content brief, which includes:\n- Logo text\n- Navigation links\n- Hero section copy\n- Feature card details\n- Footer copyright\n\nThe page is now ready in the workspace. Would you like me to explain any part of the implementation or make any specific adjustments?\n\n### html_structure\nI've created the HTML fragment for the Flowdesk landing page using the content from content.txt. The fragment includes:\n\n✅ Semantic HTML5 structure\n✅ Semantic classes: .navbar, .hero, .cta, .features, .card, .footer\n✅ Anchor links matching section IDs\n✅ Emoji icons for feature cards\n✅ Real content from the content brief\n\nKey points:\n- Header with logo and navigation links\n- Hero section with headline, subheading, and CTA\n- Features section with 3 cards\n- Footer with copyright text\n\nThe fragment is saved in html_fragment.txt, ready for the next stage of development. Would you like me to proceed with creating the full index.html with embedded CSS and JavaScript?\n\n### styling\nI've created a fully functional, res